      "rdfs:comment": [
        "NOTE: While an agreement has two or more parties, and contains commitments which bind those parties, it will not always be necessary to instantiate each individual commitment.",
        "DEFINITION: A mutually understood arrangement in which two or more parties make commitments to one another.",
        "EXAMPLE: A gym membership is an agreement in which the member commits to paying the gym a certain price and the gym commits to allowing access to their facilities."
      ],
